    "created_at": "2016-01-08T04:38:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-01-08T04:38:52Z",
    "body": "That's a good point @lukeapage. But I don't think that a false sense of security is a reason to not make improvements to security where possible.\n\nIn this case I think we could even close the hole you mention. What about, if Node integration is off in the parent, having certain features—not just `nodeIntegration`, but also `icon` and perhaps other `BrowserWindow` options—be ignored in calls to `window.open`? (And have the new window just inherit those options from the parent.)\n"
  },
